"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081831","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-07","<p>£1 billion has been provisionally allocated according to a needs-based formula. This is calculated according to metrics of: income, productivity, deprivation, skills, and the number of people living in towns.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","228029","2019-03-07T16:13:07.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081831/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081831/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081831/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-04","Stronger Towns Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what form the Government's needs-based formula to determine the allocation of the Stronger Towns Fund will take.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","228107"
