"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081834","Department for International Development","false","2019-03-07","<p>There are currently no plans to provide new funding to UK companies to deliver education services in Uganda. The UK Government is supporting more children to access good quality education in primary and secondary schools through a partnership with the Government of Uganda.</p><p> </p><p>Since January 2019, the Minister of State for Africa has not met anyone directly related to this issue.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2019-03-07T13:56:21.003Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081834/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081834/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081834/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-03-04","Uganda: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to reports in the Indian Ocean Newsletter on 22 February 2019, that the UK Government is seeking to expand the role of British companies providing education services in Uganda, what plans her Department has to provide new funding to UK companies to deliver education services in Uganda; and which organisations and individuals the Minister of State for Africa has met with since January 2019 on this issue.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","228110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081835","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-11","<p>Our recent consultation <em>Planning Reform: Supporting the high street and increasing delivery of new homes </em>set out a package of proposals to simplify and speed up the planning system, make effective use of land, help high streets to adapt and diversify and deliver more homes through new permitted development rights and changes to the Use Classes Order.</p><p>We are currently considering the responses received to the consultation. Decisions will be taken shortly on the consultation proposals to be taken forward.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","228112","2019-03-11T17:41:52.163Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081835/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081835/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081835/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-04","Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what the timetable is for the Government to publish a response to the consultation on Planning reform: supporting the high street and increasing the delivery of new homes, with particular respect to the sections relating to the expansion of permitted development rights.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","228111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081836","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-11","<p>Our recent consultation <em>Planning Reform: Supporting the high street and increasing delivery of new homes </em>set out a package of proposals to simplify and speed up the planning system, make effective use of land, help high streets to adapt and diversify and deliver more homes through new permitted development rights and changes to the Use Classes Order.</p><p>We are currently considering the responses received to the consultation. Decisions will be taken shortly on the consultation proposals to be taken forward.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","228111","2019-03-11T17:41:52.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081836/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081836/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081836/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-04","Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, when he plans to publish the Government response to the consultation entitled Planning reform: supporting the high street and increasing the delivery of new homes.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","228112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081837","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-11","<p>The national permitted development rights for change of use are making a valuable contribution to housing delivery. In the three years to March 2018, 46,000 homes were delivered under the rights, including 42,000 from office to residential. The prior approval process provides a streamlined planning process, and this is reflected in the fee. To support local planning authorities planning fees were increased by 20 per cent in 2018. This increase was ring fenced to ensure the funding benefited planning services directly. We continue to keep resourcing under review.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","228114 ; 228115","2019-03-11T17:40:14.68Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081837/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081837/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081837/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-04","Change of Use","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the financial effect on local authorities of providing services to support new development taken forward under the office to residential permitted development rights process.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","228113"
