"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081887","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-12","<p>We are in discussion with the Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport and The Royal Parks about the future maintenance arrangements for Victoria Tower Gardens.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-03-12T15:00:50.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081887/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081887/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081887/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-04","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how responsibility for maintaining Victoria Tower Gardens will be divided between Royal Parks and the body responsible for the Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre once the Memorial and Learning Centre has been built.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","227956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081888","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-12","<p>We are considering various operating models to cover the running costs which are estimated at up to £6 million per annum, and will put in place a sustainable long-term plan. While the entrance to the learning centre will be ticketed to avoid queues, no decision has yet been taken on charging policy.</p><p> </p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-03-12T14:56:31.453Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081888/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081888/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081888/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-04","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of (a) the annual running costs of the Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre and (b) how much of that cost will be covered by visitor entrance fees and other income.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","227957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081889","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-12","<p>Victoria Tower Gardens is already home to memorials commemorating past struggles for justice and democratic causes. There is no better place for the Memorial, which will stand as a fitting reminder of the horrors of the past and encourage reflection on their implications for the British government and society, both at the time and subsequently. The view of Parliament from the Memorial will serve as a permanent reminder that political decisions have far-reaching consequences.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-03-12T15:00:14.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081889/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081889/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081889/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-04","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 18 December 2018 to Question 203298, National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, what is the relevance of the Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre being located on the banks of the Thames.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","227958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081890","Home Office","false","2019-03-07","<p>The Government has been clear that there is no limit on the number of genuine international students who can come to study in the UK and there is no intention to impose one.</p><p>An EEA national who has been studying in the UK prior to applying for a visa or leave to remain for the purposes of study will be able to do so either under the current Tier 4 route or under the future system. There is no rea-son they should be unable to obtain such permission provided that they meet the requirements of the Immigration Rules at that time.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-03-07T16:50:45.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081890/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081890/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081890/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-04","Overseas Students: EEA Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 28 February 2019 to Question 225480, whether international students would be guaranteed a student visa under the new immigration system once their European Temporary Leave to Remain runs out, provided they pass an additional criminality check, without additional cost or administrative burden.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","228054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081891","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-03-12","<p>There were 3,352 FTE band 4 probation officers in post as at 31 December 2018. This figure shows a broadly stable trend with a small increase of 9 (0.3%) since 30 September 2018 and a small decrease of 17 (0.5%) compared to 31 December 2017. In the last year, 707 Probation Service Officers (PSO) were appointed, some of whom will be training to become qualified Probation Officers (PO).</p><p> </p><p>As at December 2018, there were 544 FTE probation Officers in post in the North West Probation Service Division.</p><p> </p><p>We are recruiting more staff into the National Probation Service to reduce the reliance on agency staff. Changes to the recruitment process and eligibility criteria for probation officers have been made resulting in increases in both the volume and diversity of probation officer applicants. A national campaign to recruit probation officers is currently underway and successful candidates will start in July 2019.</p><p> </p><p>HMPPS does not publish data on numbers of vacancies.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","228153","2019-03-12T17:30:21.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081891/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081891/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081891/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-03-04","Prison and Probation Service: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what progress he has made on recruiting probation officers in (a) England and (b) North West; and how many vacancies there are in each of those areas.","false","Biography information for James Frith","Bury North","James Frith","228148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081892","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-03-12","<p>Her Majesty’s Inspectorate of Probation found that the National Probation Service’s leadership team in the North West is focused on delivering a high-quality service. It assessed the work of the Division overall as “Good”.</p><p> </p><p>The Inspectorate made eight recommendations for improvement, A programme of building improvement works has already been completed and an action plan has been drawn up to address the remaining recommendations. This was sent to the Inspectorate on 4 March.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","228150 ; 228151 ; 228152","2019-03-12T17:31:17.22Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081892/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081892/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081892/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-03-04","Prison and Probation Service: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the report entitled, An inspection of North West Division National Probation Service, published by HM Inspectorate of Probation in February 2019, what steps he is taking to ensure that probation staff are trained on the policy requirements in relation to the use of remote technology.","false","Biography information for James Frith","Bury North","James Frith","228149"
