"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1079562","Home Office","false","2019-03-26","<p>Staff contracted by suppliers are required to have a minimum clearance level of Base Level Clearance (BPSS).</p><p>All roles are assessed against the security framework to establish the level of clearance required. Where deemed appropriate for the role, staff contracted by suppliers are must also successfully complete a Counter Terrorist Check (CTC) or Security Check (SC). There are no resources on the programme that require Developed Vetting (DV).</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-03-26T13:15:38.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1079562/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1079562/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1079562/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-01","Home Office: Vetting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 25 February 2019 to Question 223140 on Home Office: Staff, whether a (a) Counter Terrorist Check, (b) Security Check and (c) Developed Vetting has been required for each of the staff contracted by suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","227373"
